<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="285" pageId="4" pageNumber="284" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[835,1444,724,1921]" pageId="4" pageNumber="284">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Newman" baseAuthorityYear="1836" box="[873,1093,1151,1175]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Xanthoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="284" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis box="[873,1093,1151,1175]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="284">Xanthoperla apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a species of larger rivers in Europe (
<bibRefCitation author="Lillehammer, A." box="[942,1195,1186,1211]" pageId="4" pageNumber="284" refId="ref6201" refString="Lillehammer, A. (1988): Stoneflies (Plecoptera) of Fennoscandia and Denmark. Fauna Entomologica Scandinavica. - Scandinavian Science Press Ltd. Leiden, New York, Kobenhavn, Koln. Bd. 21: 165." type="book" year="1988">Lillehammer 1988:80</bibRefCitation>
). It was historically widespread in Europe but suffered from habitat fragmentation and has become very rare in central Europe (
<bibRefCitation author="Zwick, P." box="[935,1072,1293,1317]" pageId="4" pageNumber="284" pagination="80 - 97" refId="ref6670" refString="Zwick, P. 1992. Stream habitat fragmentation - a threat to biodiversity. Biodiversity and Conservation, 1 (2): 80 - 97." type="journal article" year="1992">Zwick 1992</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Zwick, P." box="[1083,1139,1293,1317]" pageId="4" pageNumber="284" pagination="315 - 348" refId="ref6698" refString="Zwick, P. 2004. Key to the West Palaearctic genera of stoneflies (Plecoptera) in the larval stage. Limnologica, 34 (4): 315 - 348." type="journal article" year="2004">2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Koese, B." box="[1149,1327,1293,1317]" pageId="4" pageNumber="284" refId="ref5997" refString="Koese, B. 2008. De Nederlandse steenvliegen (Plecoptera). EIS, Leiden. 158 pp." type="book" year="2008">Koese 2008:105</bibRefCitation>
). It is also rare in 
<collectingCountry box="[925,1025,1329,1353]" name="Norway" pageId="4" pageNumber="284">Norway</collectingCountry>
, with a scattered and little known distribution. The nineteenth century specimens in the NHM are listed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Brekke, R." box="[1076,1240,1400,1424]" pageId="4" pageNumber="284" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref5497" refString="Brekke, R. 1941. The Norwegian stoneflies. Plecoptera. Norsk Entomologisk Tidsskrift, 6 (1): 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="1941">Brekke (1941)</bibRefCitation>
under the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Bengtsson, 1933" authorityName="Bengtsson" authorityYear="1933" box="[835,1266,1435,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Chloroperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="284" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borealis">
<emphasis box="[835,1055,1435,1459]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="284">Chloroperla borealis</emphasis>
Bengtsson, 1933
</taxonomicName>
. According to Brekke, 
<bibRefCitation author="Schoyen, W. M." box="[947,1140,1471,1495]" pageId="4" pageNumber="284" pagination="1 - 30" refId="ref6346" refString="Schoyen, W. M. 1887. Fortegnelse over de i Norge hidtil observerede Neuroptera Planipennia og Pseudo-Neuroptera. Forhandlinger i Videnskapsselskapet i Christiana aar 1887, 13: 1 - 30." type="journal article" year="1887">Schøyen (1887)</bibRefCitation>
refers to these same specimens under the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Newm. Schoyen" authorityName="Newm. Schoyen" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Isopteryx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="284" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis box="[1160,1348,1506,1530]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="284">Isopteryx apicalis</emphasis>
Newm. Schøyen
</taxonomicName>
does not cite specimens explicitly, but lists the municipalities Christiania (= 
<collectingRegion box="[1209,1265,1577,1601]" country="Norway" name="Oslo" pageId="4" pageNumber="284">Oslo</collectingRegion>
), Ringerike and Elverum. 
<bibRefCitation author="Brittain, J. E." box="[967,1146,1613,1637]" pageId="4" pageNumber="284" pagination="52 - 53" refId="ref5549" refString="Brittain, J. E. 1983. The first record of the nymph of Xanthoperla apicalis (Newman) (Plecoptera: Chloroperlidae) from Scandinavia, with a key to the mature nymphs of the Scandinavian Chloroperlidae. Fauna Norvegica Serie B, 30 (1): 52 - 53." type="journal article" year="1983">Brittain (1983</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Brittain, J. E. &amp; A. Lillehammer &amp; R. Bildeng" box="[1173,1434,1613,1637]" pageId="4" pageNumber="284" pagination="189 - 199" refId="ref5603" refString="Brittain, J. E., A. Lillehammer, &amp; R. Bildeng. 1984. The impact of a water transfer scheme on the benthic macroinvertebrates of a Norwegian river. p. 189 - 199. In: A. Lillehammer &amp; S. Saltveit [editors] Regulated Rivers. Universitetsforlaget, Oslo [etc]." type="book chapter" year="1984">Brittain et al. 1984</bibRefCitation>
) discusses finds from the Namsen and Sanddøla rivers in Nord Trondelag, as well as the river Glomma in 
<collectingRegion box="[978,1096,1719,1743]" country="Norway" name="Hedmark" pageId="4" pageNumber="284">Hedmark</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[835,1444,724,1921]" lastBlockId="5.[189,797,1397,1598]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="285" pageId="4" pageNumber="284">
Note: 
<bibRefCitation author="Zwick, P." box="[950,1107,1755,1779]" pageId="4" pageNumber="284" pagination="315 - 348" refId="ref6698" refString="Zwick, P. 2004. Key to the West Palaearctic genera of stoneflies (Plecoptera) in the larval stage. Limnologica, 34 (4): 315 - 348." type="journal article" year="2004">Zwick (2004)</bibRefCitation>
remarks that figure 
<quantity box="[1368,1442,1755,1779]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8956" pageId="4" pageNumber="284" unit="in" value="114.0">114 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Lillehammer, A." box="[835,1098,1790,1814]" pageId="4" pageNumber="284" refId="ref6201" refString="Lillehammer, A. (1988): Stoneflies (Plecoptera) of Fennoscandia and Denmark. Fauna Entomologica Scandinavica. - Scandinavian Science Press Ltd. Leiden, New York, Kobenhavn, Koln. Bd. 21: 165." type="book" year="1988">Lillehammer (1988:76)</bibRefCitation>
does not show the pronotum of 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" box="[872,990,1826,1850]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Isopteryx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="284" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis box="[872,990,1826,1850]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="284">X. apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The NHM slide collection includes three slides marked ‘P39 
<emphasis box="[1171,1301,1861,1885]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="284">X. apicalis’</emphasis>
, bearing a nymphal hind leg, cerci, two heads, one pronotum and a complete small nymph. The incomplete collecting event data associated with P39 is ‘Storelva, 
<date box="[189,306,1468,1492]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="1966-04-26">26.iv.1966</date>
’. The pronota in these slides do not look like Lillehammer’s fig. 114. However, they are probably 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zwick" authorityYear="1967" box="[323,463,1539,1563]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Siphonoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[323,463,1539,1563]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">Siphonoperla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Peter Zwick, personal communication 
<date box="[380,570,1574,1598]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="2011-09">September 2011</date>
).
</paragraph>
